      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Treatment of an <i>α</i>,<i>β</i>-unsaturated ketone with basic aqueous hydrogen peroxide yields an epoxy ketone. The reaction is specific to unsaturated ketones; isolated alkene double bonds do not react. Propose a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbG9XIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ffd20f6062ae5e05e945ed8b0e1e488d8ca0efac/OChem_19_EC_039.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows 2-cyclohexenone with hydrogen peroxide, sodium hydroxide, and water to yield an epoxy ketone, where the cyclohexanone ring is fused with oxirane at the second and third carbons.\">",
